qas.question: What kind of human lives by collecting wild flora and fauna?

context: A <a0_0><b6_0>hunter-gatherer<b6_0/><a0_0/> is a human living in a society in which most or all food is obtained by <b3_0><b4_0>foraging<b4_0/><b3_0/> (collecting wild plants and pursuing wild animals), in contrast to <a1_0><b5_0><b7_0>agricultural<b7_0/><b5_0/><a1_0/> societies, which rely mainly on <a2_0>domesticated species<a2_0/>.
